I am trying to get the “shooterMotorGroup” to run from the match time of 0.7 seconds to 1 second in the autonomous period. The program currently does not run those motors at all.
After some messing around with it, I have gotten it to run only after 0.7 seconds, but not stopping.
This is occurs in lines 71-74 of my program.

Any help is greatly appreciated.

Try changing it to something more like
if (Timer.getMatchTime() > 0.7 &&Timer.getMatchTime < 1) { shooterMotorControllerGroup.set(0.8); } else { shooterMotorControllerGroup.set(0); }
This will only run the shooter motors between .7 and 1 second. Your current code’s issue is that if the the time is, say, .8, the shooter motors will start. But if the time is, say, 1.1, the condition in the second half will fail, but it also won’t even get checked because 1.1>.7.
The code above fixes that issue; if the time is between .7 and 1 it will spin the shooter; otherwise, it will stop it.
